      "content": "Taking two doses of lisinopril at once is not recommended and can be dangerous. The medication is designed to be taken once daily to maintain consistent blood pressure levels. Doubling up can lead to unpredictable fluctuations in blood pressure, potentially causing serious health issues such as dizziness, fainting, or even a heart attack. It's important to stick to the prescribed dosage to avoid these risks. If you miss a dose, take it as soon as you remember, but do not double up. Your health is too important to risk. Please consult your doctor if you have any concerns about your medication.",
